<section class="py-16 px-4 bg-white dark:bg-slate-900">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-4 text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-100">
      The Problem with Requirements Today
    </h2>
    <p class="text-center text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-10 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      Teams spend weeks writing requirements that are ignored, misunderstood, or immediately outdated. AI tools hallucinate without structure.
    </p>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800">
        <div class="text-3xl mb-3">📝</div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-100">Vague Requirements</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">Ambiguous user stories lead to misaligned implementations and endless revision cycles.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800">
        <div class="text-3xl mb-3">🤖</div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-100">AI Without Structure</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">LLMs produce inconsistent results when given unstructured prompts. Structure enables repeatability.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800">
        <div class="text-3xl mb-3">🔄</div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-100">No Validation Loop</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">Without automated acceptance criteria, there's no way to know if what was built matches what was specified.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
